academicProgress: During the academic year, the college successfully introduced new academic programs aligned with national and international standards. Curriculum revision was undertaken to integrate modern pedagogical approaches and outcome-based learning practices. Continuous assessment and remedial classes were implemented to improve student performance and overall results. Faculty development workshops and training sessions were also conducted to enhance teaching quality and academic excellence.
researchProgress: The college has actively promoted a research-driven academic culture. Several faculty- and student-led research projects were completed during the year, some of which were published in reputed journals. The college hosted national-level seminars and conferences to foster academic exchange and innovation. Initiatives for establishing research collaborations and pursuing research grants were also strengthened, further encouraging innovation and interdisciplinary research activities.
adminProgress: Administrative processes were streamlined through digitalization and policy refinement. The college formed new committees to enhance transparency, accountability, and participatory decision-making. Regular meetings and audits ensured effective monitoring of institutional activities. Efforts were made to improve inter-departmental coordination and communication, leading to better governance and operational efficiency.
qualityProgress: The college continued to prioritize quality assurance through active engagement with QAAC guidelines. Internal Quality Assurance mechanisms were strengthened, and feedback systems for students, faculty, and stakeholders were effectively implemented. Periodic evaluations and peer reviews were carried out to maintain high academic and institutional standards. Quality enhancement training sessions were also organized to ensure continuous improvement in teaching, learning, and administration.
majorChallenges: The college encountered challenges such as resource limitations, increasing student enrollment without proportional infrastructure expansion, and delays in policy approvals. Recruitment of qualified faculty in specialized disciplines and adapting to rapid technological changes also remained key concerns. Despite these issues, the college managed to sustain academic quality and operational stability through effective planning and teamwork.
nextYearPlan: The college aims to expand research and innovation activities, strengthen digital learning infrastructure, and establish stronger industry-academic partnerships. Plans include launching new skill-oriented programs, upgrading laboratories and libraries, and implementing advanced student support systems. Strategic goals are closely aligned with Tribhuvan University’s vision for quality education, innovation, and inclusive growth.

researchProgress: The institution continued to promote a strong research culture. adminProgress: Administrative operations were streamlined through the implementation of a digital document management system, which reduced paperwork and improved efficiency. qualityProgress: The Quality Assurance and Accreditation Cell (QAAC) conducted internal audits and facilitated workshops on self-assessment report (SAR) preparation. nextYearPlan:

Establishing a Research Collaboration Office to enhance partnerships and grant acquisition.

Expanding the student support and counseling system to improve retention and well-being.

Fully implementing the digital governance system for administrative transparency.

Continuing professional development programs for faculty and staff.

Strengthening the internal quality assurance mechanism and preparing for external accreditation.

academicProgress: यस शैक्षिक वर्षमा विश्वविद्यालयका विभिन्न संकाय तथा विभागहरूबाट नयाँ शैक्षिक कार्यक्रमहरू सुरु गरिएका छन्, जसले शिक्षार्थीहरूलाई वर्तमान बजार र प्रविधिको मागअनुसारको दक्षता विकासमा सहयोग पुर्‍याएको छ। पाठ्यक्रमको पुनरावलोकन र अद्यावधिक कार्य नियमित रूपमा सञ्चालन गरिएको छ, जस अन्तर्गत शिक्षक, विद्यार्थी, र विषयविज्ञहरूबीचको परामर्शद्वारा विषयवस्तुहरूको प्रासंगिकता सुनिश्चित गरिएको छ। साथै, मूल्यांकन प्रणाली सुधार, कक्षा नियमितता, र सहपाठ्य क्रियाकलापहरूको सुदृढीकरणले विद्यार्थीहरूको नतिजामा उल्लेखनीय सुधार ल्याएको छ।
researchProgress: यो वर्ष विभिन्न विभागहरूद्वारा उल्लेखनीय अनुसन्धान परियोजनाहरू सम्पन्न गरिएका छन्। केही अनुसन्धान प्रतिवेदनहरू राष्ट्रिय तथा अन्तर्राष्ट्रिय जर्नलहरूमा प्रकाशित भएका छन्। विश्वविद्यालयस्तरीय अनुसन्धान सम्मेलन र कार्यशालाहरू आयोजना गरिएका छन् जसले शिक्षक तथा विद्यार्थीबीच अनुसन्धानसंस्कृति विकासमा टेवा पुर्‍याएको छ। साथै, केही अनुसन्धान कार्यहरूबाट पेटेन्ट दर्ता प्रक्रियासमेत प्रारम्भ गरिएको छ, जसले संस्थाको नवप्रवर्तन क्षमतामा वृद्धि गरेको छ।
adminProgress: यस वर्ष विश्वविद्यालयले आन्तरिक प्रशासनिक प्रक्रियामा पारदर्शिता र दक्षता वृद्धि गर्न विभिन्न नीति तथा दिशानिर्देशहरू अद्यावधिक गरेको छ। प्रशासनिक कार्यप्रवाहलाई डिजिटाइज गर्न सुरु गरिएको छ, जसले समय र स्रोतको बचतका साथै कार्यगत प्रभावकारिता बढाएको छ। आवश्यक समितिहरूको गठन, आन्तरिक अनुगमन प्रणाली सुदृढीकरण, र कर्मचारी क्षमता विकास तालिमका माध्यमबाट संस्थाको सुशासन स्तरमा उल्लेखनीय सुधार आएको छ।
qualityProgress: गुणस्तर आश्वासन तथा प्रमाणीकरण समिति (QAAC) को संयोजनमा गुणस्तर मूल्याङ्कन सम्बन्धी विभिन्न गतिविधिहरू सम्पन्न गरिएका छन्। विद्यार्थी तथा शिक्षक प्रतिक्रिया संकलन प्रणाली कार्यान्वयनमा ल्याइएको छ, जसको आधारमा शैक्षिक गुणस्तर सुधारका योजनाहरू निर्माण गरिएका छन्। नियमित आन्तरिक मूल्याङ्कन, सहकर्मी मूल्याङ्कन, र स्वमूल्याङ्कन प्रणालीहरूलाई सुदृढ गर्दै संस्थाको निरन्तर सुधार सुनिश्चित गरिएको छ।
majorChallenges: यस वर्षका प्रमुख चुनौतीहरूमा स्रोत र पूर्वाधारको अभाव, योग्य जनशक्तिको सीमितता, अनुसन्धानका लागि पर्याप्त बजेटको कमी, र प्रविधि एकीकरणमा आउने कठिनाइहरू समावेश छन्। साथै, नयाँ कार्यक्रम सञ्चालनका लागि आवश्यक स्वीकृति प्रक्रिया लामो हुनु र समयमै सामग्री आपूर्तिमा ढिलाइ हुनु पनि प्रमुख अवरोधहरू बनेका छन्।
nextYearPlan: आगामी वर्षमा शिक्षण–अधिगम प्रणालीलाई अझ प्रभावकारी बनाउन सूचना प्रविधि–आधारित शिक्षण विधि विस्तार गरिनेछ। अनुसन्धान र नवप्रवर्तनमा जोड दिई, अन्तरविभागीय परियोजनाहरू सञ्चालन गरिनेछ। प्रशासनिक स्वचालन (automation) र नीतिगत स्पष्टता मार्फत सुशासन सुदृढ गरिने योजना छ। गुणस्तर आश्वासनका मापदण्डहरू थप कार्यान्वयन गर्दै, विद्यार्थी सन्तुष्टि र शैक्षिक उत्कृष्टता बढाउने दिशा लिइनेछ। साथै, अवरोध र चुनौतीहरू समाधान गर्न दीर्घकालीन पूर्वाधार र जनशक्ति विकासमा लगानी गरिनेछ।

academicProgress: During the reporting period, significant strides were made in strengthening academic and curricular development. Several new programs were launched to align with national priorities and emerging global trends, ensuring that our graduates remain competitive in a rapidly evolving job market. Curriculum reviews were carried out across multiple faculties, focusing on modernizing course content, integrating digital literacy, and embedding research-oriented and practical learning components. Continuous assessments and innovative teaching approaches contributed to a notable improvement in student results and overall academic performance. Faculty development workshops were also conducted to enhance teaching quality and pedagogical innovation.
researchProgress: The institution demonstrated commendable progress in research and innovation this year. A number of research projects were completed, addressing national development challenges and contributing valuable insights to academia and industry. Faculty and students actively participated in national and international conferences, presenting papers and sharing findings that reflect the university’s growing research capacity. Efforts were made to strengthen research collaborations and establish linkages with external partners. Moreover, initiatives were taken to promote innovation and intellectual property development, resulting in the registration of patents and new prototypes that have practical application potential.
adminProgress: In line with our goal of fostering transparency and efficiency, several administrative and governance reforms were introduced. Updated policies and operational guidelines were implemented to improve institutional management, decision-making, and accountability. The use of digital systems was expanded for record keeping, communication, and data-driven decision processes. Various committees and working groups were formed to ensure participatory governance, streamline processes, and enhance coordination across departments. Administrative staff received capacity-building training to further strengthen institutional governance.
qualityProgress: Continuous quality assurance and enhancement remained a core focus throughout the year. The QAAC (Quality Assurance and Accreditation Committee) activities were intensified, including self-assessment reporting and preparation for external peer reviews. Mechanisms for student and stakeholder feedback were strengthened to inform academic and administrative improvements. Workshops on internal quality culture, learning outcome measurement, and continuous improvement practices were organized. These efforts have collectively contributed to fostering a culture of excellence, accountability, and evidence-based improvement across all levels of operation.
majorChallenges: Despite notable progress, several challenges were encountered during the reporting period. Limited financial resources, delays in administrative processes, and insufficient infrastructure constrained the pace of program implementation. Human resource gaps, especially in technical and research positions, posed difficulties in meeting growing academic demands. Additionally, adapting to rapid technological changes and maintaining digital readiness across faculties required significant effort. Coordination across departments and ensuring consistent policy compliance also remained a concern.
nextYearPlan:
Looking ahead, the institution aims to consolidate achievements and address identified challenges through a well-defined action plan. Key priorities include:

Expanding new academic programs in high-demand and interdisciplinary areas.

Enhancing research capacity through dedicated grants, collaborations, and research labs.

Strengthening e-governance and digital transformation across administrative units.

Advancing quality assurance through continuous monitoring, feedback integration, and capacity development.

Upgrading infrastructure and learning resources to support modern pedagogy.

Fostering partnerships with national and international institutions for academic and research excellence.
